code_changes.content:
[
  {
    "file": "lib/vtls/openssl.c",
    "line": 992,
    "severity": "high",
    "description": "Missing NULL check for 'global_passwd' parameter in passwd_callback() before calling strlen(). When OpenSSL invokes this callback for an encrypted private key but no password has been configured, 'global_passwd' is NULL. Calling strlen(NULL) results in undefined behavior (typically a crash). The fix adds '&& global_passwd' to the condition guard so strlen is only called when the pointer is non-NULL.",
    "fix_applied": true
  },
  {
    "file": "lib/base64.c",
    "line": 200,
    "severity": "medium",
    "description": "In base64_encode(), when 'insize' is 0 the code falls through to 'insize = strlen(inputbuff)'. If the caller passes insize=0 with a NULL inputbuff (valid since zero length means no data to encode), this calls strlen(NULL), which is undefined behavior and typically crashes. The fix returns CURLE_OK immediately when insize is 0, treating zero-length input as producing zero-length output.",
    "fix_applied": true
  }
]

